text.tspan: Daily confirmed COVID-19 cases, rolling 3-day average
The number of confirmed cases is lower than the number of total cases. The main reason for this is limited testing.
Source: European CDC – Situation Update Worldwide – Last updated 27th April, 11:15 (London time)
Note: The rolling average is the average across three days – the confirmed cases on the particular date, and the previous two days. For
example, the value for 27th March is the average over the 25th, 26th and 27th March.
